cs.SC, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the method of creative telescoping, which is a crucial tool in computer-generated proofs of combinatorial and special-function identities. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for creative telescoping and the problem of constructing telescopers efficiently. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon the complexity of the algorithms for creative telescoping. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper may involve logical reasoning in the proof of the existence criteria for telescopers. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category, but cannot be completely ruled out as the paper may involve geometric interpretations of the trivariate rational functions.
